Package: politicaldata
Type: Package
Title: Package To Acquire And Analyze Political Data
Version: 0.1.0
Author: G. Elliott Morris
Maintainer: G. Elliott Morris <elliott@thecrosstab.com>
Description: This package provides a consolidated location for useful functions and interfaces to common sources of data used in politics and political science.
    Examples include: Polls (such as the American National Election Studies and Cooperative Congressional Election Studies), polling aggregators (like RealClearPolitics, HuffingtonPost Pollster and FiveThirtyEight), election results, congressional boundaries, legislator ideological scores.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: 
    dplyr,
    tidyr,
    ggplot2,
    utils
Suggests: 
    testthat
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
